The R 4.5 release is this Friday April 11.

More over,   it will not be available via BiocManager in devel because it needs to build on our builders.  It is failing across all
https://bioconductor.org/checkResults/devel/bioc-LATEST/RbowtieCuda/

 but that is expected because of the Nvidia GPU/cuda requirement as you experienced in the review process as we had to set up an entirely different environment/builder for testing.

This should have been conveyed on the issue and I'm sorry it was not.  We have a plan that should not take very long to implement to add propagation from the GPU builders used in the review process.  However given that is a week before our semi-annual release we are at capacity to add this new integration until after the release next week.

Finally,
In seems this thread was linked by responding to a different thread regarding the conference abstracts.  Please do not reply to other threads to post new comments unless it is relevant to that thread.  Please send a new email to bioc-devel at r-projects so we can keep threads distinct and organized.



